{% extends 'layout.html.twig' %}
{% set active = 'doc' %}

{% block content %}

    <h2>{{ 'Yaskef User Guide'|trans }}</h2>

    <h3>PHP snippets</h3>

    <p>In PHP mode, just type some PHP code in the code field, then click
    "Test" to see the result.
    </p>
    <pre>&lt:?php
echo 'Hello, World!';</pre>

    <p>Yaskef as already put the open_tag <code>&lt;?php</code> for you,
    event if it will be removed before sending your code to eval; it is only
    mandatory for the <a href="http://codemirror.net/" class="ext">Code Mirror</a> editor
    to show a correct syntax highlight.<br/>
    If you need to put some html, you can leave the PHP mode
    with <code>?&gt;</code>.</p>
    <p class="note"> A final <code>&lt;?php&nbsp;</code> for returning in PHP mode
    is not mandatory.
    </p>
    <pre>&lt;?php
echo 'Hello, World';
?&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;a href="http://electrolinux.github.com/yaskef/"&gt;Yaskef is cool&lt;/a&gt;</pre>

    <p class="note">Mixed content, <code>use </code> or <code>namespace </code>
    is not passed to the minimalistic/simplistic syntax checker.
    </p>

    <h3>Javascript snippets</h3>

    <p>
        The javascript code is simply put inside a
        <code>&lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;</code> tag.<br/>
        If some html is needed, it can be put in the html field, wich is
        then put just before script tag.
    </p>

    <p>
        You can use the preloaded jquery 1.7 in your code.
    </p>

    <pre>$(function(){
    $("body").css('backgroundColor','#ff9900');
});</pre>

    <h3>SQL snippets</h3>

    <p>Not very well tested, the SQL code is passed to the DBAL implementation
    choosen in prod.php.<br/>
    The default database is sqlite3. Other doctrine databases have not been
    tested yet.
    </p>
    <pre>SELECT id,lang,name,rows FROM snippet ORDER BY lang,name;</pre>

    <h3>Pastebin</h3>

    <p>
        If you have an account at <a href="http://pastebin.com/">pastebin.com</a>,
        and have created your user with the --pastebin option, you should have
        a "Paste to pastebin.com" button.
    </p>

    <p>
        You can choose the exposure and expiration you want for your paste
        by going to the profile page.
    </p>

